            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Alexander Gertner</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#gertnerA" start="2991.868" end="x">Yes. We were [unfinished word]...but I worked. From one machine to another. I was sent from one place to another. It lasted three months. Three months I worked in the...the DAW. And there were already too many people. Sometimes this happened, that they sent [too many], because they didn't know what to do with the people. There were so many people they didn't have some kind of work to give them. The work was tossed around. It was like this there. We worked there on Sunday. Well, six days a week we worked for eleven hours, and on Sunday we worked...every second Sunday and sometimes every Sunday. We had to...the Sunday work was even more terrible for us that the whole week.</span>
        </li>
