            <span class="utterance" who="#gertnerA" start="4000.653" end="x">The women also marched. They were in <a class="placename" href="#vothC10" type="camp">Birkenau</a>, in another <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>. And so on the 18th of January we went away, on Thursday afternoon. I remember, in the heaviest snow we march at night. We don't know where we are going, with things which we had with us. And we marched like this for two days and two nights. In front of us marched the women from <a class="placename" href="#vothC10" type="camp">Birkenau</a>. We marched altogether thirty thousand people. <a class="placename" href="#vothC10" type="camp">Birkenau</a> went. <a class="placename" href="#vothC18" type="camp">Buna</a> was another <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>.</span>
