            <span class="utterance" who="#gertnerA" start="4430.233" end="x">And so we were there in Gross-...we were loca-...there were terribly many people. We were disembarked to be distributed. We were terribly many people. They yelled for us to form a line. People were hungry, and one didn't know what to do. Later, after we had stayed there overnight in that <a class="term" href="#vothG_block">block</a>, twelve hundred people, in the morning we were again told to get up, early around two [a.m.], to fetch something to eat. At that time there was brought something like water made out of grits [?]. It looked like water from the grits [word mispronouced].</span>
