            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#gertnerA" start="5272.204" end="x">With the cudgel on the face. He didn't even look. On the face [?]. On the face, everywhere. 'I'll beat you here. Here you will drop.' He says, 'Here I beat you. Here you shall drop. Why did you [take] bread?' I say, 'No, Herr <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a> elder, I got bread.' I still had on me the piece of bread that we took along from the <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>. 'Yes, you did take.' He beats me up so much that I thought [?] now I am finished [Footnote: It is characteristic that all through these interviews it appears that the Nazis could not bring themselves to use the verb steal in connection with the word bread. Even in a case of execution of several prisoners who took bread from the kitchen during an air-raid alarm, the term Brot nehmen [take bread] was used and not Brot stehlen [steal bread]. --DPB.].</span>
